%% Diagram: IndexedDB transaction lifecycle and the auto-commit trap
%% Type: stateDiagram
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false, 'flowchart': {'htmlLabels': false}}}%%
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> Active: db.transaction(stores, mode)
    Active --> Active: store.put / get / index ops
    Active --> Inactive: control returns to event loop
    Inactive --> Active: success/error event for a pending request
    Inactive --> Committed: no pending requests, event loop idle
    Active --> Committed: tx.commit() called explicitly
    Active --> Aborted: tx.abort() or write error
    Inactive --> Aborted: write error on pending request
    Committed --> [*]
    Aborted --> [*]

    note right of Inactive
        Any await on a non-IDB
        promise lands here.
        New IDB ops throw
        TransactionInactiveError.
    end note
